Package: swaoBN
Title: Survey-Weighted, Covariate-Adjusted Ordinal Bayesian Network Learning
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Soumik", "Purkayastha", email = "soumik@pitt.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Implements swa-oBN (Survey-Weighted, Covariate-Adjusted Ordinal
    Bayesian Network), a method for causal discovery from complex survey data
    with ordinal variables. The method extends the ordinal causal discovery
    framework of Ni and Mallick (2022) with: (a) covariate adjustment via
    ordinal regression, (b) survey weights with effective sample size in the
    BIC penalty, (c) expert constraints via blacklists and whitelists, and
    (d) two-step scoring that separates skeleton discovery (penalized pseudo-BIC)
    from edge orientation (unpenalized pseudo-likelihood ratio). This separation
    ensures DAG selection consistency for heterogeneous ordinal levels.
